The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Rule to combat copycats on cards
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Rule to combat copycats on cards
          SHEENA K.                              
	Raipur, July 10: Attempt to either help or take help from fellow students may land an examinee behind bars in Chhattisgarh.         
	The state government will enforce an act that will ensure imprisonment and a heavy penalty for students caught using unfair means in examination halls.         
	According to official sources, Chhattisgarh cabinet recently gave its nod to the proposal to enact a law to keep a check on copycats. The government will bring the legislation in the monsoon session of the Chhattisgarh Assembly to make it an act, a source added.         
	Teachers or persons caught helping examinees would also be liable to punishment under the parameters of the act. The rule would be applicable to all examinations, including school, college, professional and competitive tests, conducted in the state.                                                                                                                                                                          
